headline: Lennar Fourth-Quarter Profit Falls as Housing Market Remains Stagnant
summary: Lennar  logged lower profit in its latest quarter as the company continued to offer incentives to drive sales in a stagnant housing market.  The homebuilder said Tuesday the market remained challenged in the quarter even as interest rates moved slightly lower, hurt by affordability concerns, weak consumer confidence and the government shutdown.  In an effort to maintain sales momentum, the company continued to use incentives like mortgage rate buydowns, pushing home deliveries up 4% while average sales price fell.
